<body>
    <h1>TCP Client (Enterprise only)</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"TCPClient(Enterpriseonly)-Backgroundandstrategicfit:">Background =
and strategic fit:</h2>
<ul>
<li>TCP Client feed is available in Velocity on Enterprise only</li>
<li>Initial release/design of this feed provides partial equivalency with t=
he related feed in GeoEvent Server.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"TCPClient(Enterpriseonly)-TestingResources:">Testing Resources:</=
h2>
<p>To test TCP Client feed, you can run a Python script like the one below =
and use the IP and port numbers as the parameters to the TCP Client feed or=
 you can use a tool like SocketTest.&nbsp; Both approaches will simulate a =
TCP Server, which sends data to the TCP Client feed in Velocity.</p>
<p>When configuring the TCP Client feed in Velocity, it makes a connection =
to the TCP Server and ensures that it is available and ready to receive dat=
a. This means that the TCP Server has to be running&nbsp;<em>before&nbsp;</=
em>you configure the TCP Client feed.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<h4 id=3D"TCPClient(Enterpriseonly)-PythonScriptApproach">Python Script App=
roach</h4>
<ul>
<li>Pre-requisite: have Python installed on the machine.&nbsp; If you need =
to <a href=3D"https://confluencewikidev.esri.com/(https:/www.python.org/dow=
nloads/" rel=3D"nofollow"> install</a> Python, check the box to "Add Python=
 to PATH" during the install process.</li>
<li>Delimited Data:=20
<ul>
<li>Comma, pipe, semi-colon, and tab are the default delimiters supported b=
y Velocity.&nbsp;</li>
<li>When sending delimited data only, each message/record must be separated=
 by a delimiter so that the TCP client knows where one message ends and ano=
ther beings.&nbsp; The script uses a newling "\n" as the delimiter, but thi=
s can be adjusted in the <code>recordTerminator</code>&nbsp; variable</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p>To use the script:</p>
<ul>
<li>You must run the Python script on a machine that is accessible to the m=
achine that is running Velocity on Enterprise.&nbsp; The script below is co=
nfigured to run on the same machine that has VoE installed (and uses 127.0.=
0.1 which is localhost).&nbsp; If you run the script on a different machine=
, you'll want to update the IP address accordingly.</li>
<li>Script is designed so that you can specify the kind of data to send (<c=
ode>esriJSON</code> , <code>JSON</code> , <code>XML</code> , <code>delimite=
dComma</code> , <code>delimitedPipe</code> , <code>delimitedSemiColon</code=
> , <code>delimitedTab, etc.)</code></li>
<li>To change the kind of data that is sent, edit the <code>message</code>&=
nbsp; variable</li>
<li>The script will send the same message on repeat, every 1 second</li>
<li>Once your Python script is running, you'll create a TCP Feed in V4E and=
 use the same IP address and Port that is used in the Python script.&nbsp;&=
nbsp;</li>
<li>If manually configuring the feed, you'll notice that the Python script =
sends a print statement that a resource has connected</li>
<li>If manually configuring the feed, you'll notice during sampleMessages t=
hat you will get print statements of the data that is sent and used to deri=
ve the feed schema</li>
<li>Once the TCP Client feed is running inV4E, you will see that the same p=
oint is sent on repeat.&nbsp; The point is in the Redlands area.</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">Expand for Python script</b><span class=3D"collapse=
-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-contr=
ol-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand sourc=
e</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: true; theme: Confluence; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Conflu=
ence">import socket
import time

HOST =3D '127.0.0.1'  # Standard loopback interface address (localhost)
PORT =3D 5005        # Port to listen on (non-privileged ports are &gt; 102=
3)
INTERVAL_SECONDS =3D 1
RECORD_TERMINATOR=3D b"\n"

esriJSON =3D"""{
  "geometryType": "esriGeometryPoint",
  "spatialReference": {
    "wkid": 4326
  },
  "features": [
    {
      "geometry": {
        "x": -117.18,
        "y": 34.055564
      },
      "attributes": {
        "stringField": "This is EsriJSON",
        "int32Field": 5,
        "int64Field": 5555555,
        "float32Field": -117.18,
        "float64Field": 34.055564,
        "dateField": 1752779083,
        "booleanField": true
      }
    }
  ]
}
"""

delimitedPipe =3D"This is a delimitedPipe|5|2222222|1756136797208|true|-117=
.18,34.055564"
delimitedComma =3D"""This is a delimitedComma,5,1111111,1752779083,True,"LI=
NESTRING (-121.49 38.58, -117.18 34.05)" """
delimitedSemiColon =3D"This is a delimitedSemiColon;5;333333;-117.18;34.055=
564;1752779083;true;POLYGON ((-127.617188 31.203405, -110.302734 30.902225,=
 -120.629883 43.580391, -127.617188 31.203405))"=20
delimitedTab =3D "This is a delimitedTab=095=09333333=09-117.18=0934.055564=
=091752779083=09true=09MULTIPOINT ((-121.49 38.58), (-117.18 34.05))"
delimitedSemiColonEnvelopeGeometry =3D """0;FALSE;Zero;3.488872444;0.438408=
905;{"xmin":-121.461953630263,"ymin":38.6654842756241,"xmax":-120.011039685=
427,"ymax":39.4787725848045, "spatialReference": { "wkid": 4269}} """

XML =3D"""
&lt;features&gt;
  &lt;feature&gt;
    &lt;stringField&gt;This is XML&lt;/stringField&gt;
    &lt;int32Field&gt;5&lt;/int32Field&gt;
    &lt;int64Field&gt;5555555&lt;/int64Field&gt;
    &lt;float32Field&gt;-117.18&lt;/float32Field&gt;
    &lt;float64Field&gt;34.055564&lt;/float64Field&gt;
    &lt;dateField&gt;1752779083&lt;/dateField&gt;
    &lt;booleanField&gt;true&lt;/booleanField&gt;
  &lt;/feature&gt;
&lt;/features&gt;
"""

XML_objectFlattening=3D"""
&lt;customers&gt;
   &lt;customer id=3D"55000"&gt;
      &lt;start_time&gt;01/01/2015 16:40:20&lt;/start_time&gt;
      &lt;end_time&gt;09/09/2025 18:40:20&lt;/end_time&gt;
      &lt;name&gt;Charter Group&lt;/name&gt;
      &lt;address&gt;
         &lt;street&gt;100 Main&lt;/street&gt;
         &lt;city&gt;Framingham&lt;/city&gt;
         &lt;state&gt;MA&lt;/state&gt;
         &lt;zip&gt;01701&lt;/zip&gt;
      &lt;/address&gt;
   &lt;/customer&gt;
&lt;/customers&gt;
"""

XML_arrayFlattening=3D"""
&lt;flight&gt;
    &lt;aircraftData&gt;
=09&lt;aircraftID&gt;N-X-211&lt;/aircraftID&gt;
=09&lt;pilot&gt;Charles L.&lt;/pilot&gt;
=09&lt;speed&gt;212.28&lt;/speed&gt;
=09&lt;altitude&gt;20200&lt;/altitude&gt;
=09&lt;heading&gt;44.02&lt;/heading&gt;
=09&lt;latitude&gt;52.653726&lt;/latitude&gt;
=09&lt;longitude&gt;-21.885421&lt;/longitude&gt;
=09&lt;status&gt;In flight&lt;/status&gt;
=09&lt;datetime&gt;1589962024&lt;/datetime&gt;
=09&lt;tags&gt;
=09    &lt;tag n=3D"0"&gt;boeing&lt;/tag&gt;
=09    &lt;tag n=3D"1"&gt;vtol&lt;/tag&gt;
=09    &lt;tag n=3D"2"&gt;glider&lt;/tag&gt;
=09&lt;/tags&gt;
=09&lt;setting&gt;
=09    &lt;value&gt;3&lt;/value&gt;
=09    &lt;value&gt;2&lt;/value&gt;
=09    &lt;value&gt;1&lt;/value&gt;
=09&lt;/setting&gt;
    &lt;/aircraftData&gt;
&lt;/flight&gt;
"""

geoJSON =3D"""{
  "type": "FeatureCollection",
  "features": [
    {
      "type": "Feature",
      "properties": {
        "stringField": "This is geoJSON",
        "int32Field": 5,
        "int64Field": 5555555,
        "float32Field": -117.18,
        "float64Field": 34.055564,
        "dateField": 1752779083,
        "booleanField": true
      },
      "geometry": {
        "type": "Point",
        "coordinates": [-117.18,34.055564],
        "crs": {
          "type": "name",
          "properties": {
            "name": "EPSG:4326"
          }
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
"""

JSON =3D"""{
"stringField": "This is JSON",
"int32Field": 5,
"int64Field": 5555555,
"float32Field": -117.18,
"float64Field": 34.055564,
"dateField": 1752779083,
"booleanField": true
}
"""

JSON_objectFlattening=3D"""[{
  "vehicleID": "17256",
  "driverName": "Peter Jones",
  "position": {
    "latitude": 35.21027,
    "longitude": -81.291326
  },
  "vehicleInformation": {
    "lastService": 1571431836,
    "warningCodes": 2
  },
  "speed": 64.3
}]"""

JSON_arrayFlattening=3D"""{
    "name": "iss",
    "id": 25544,
    "latitude": -13.210305423781,
    "longitude": -118.47517068897,
    "velocity": 27564.442053654,
    "visibility": "daylight",
    "cargoInformation": [{
            "sensorsID": 1,
            "age": 5432
        }, {
            "sensorsID": 2,
            "age": 9876
        }
    ],
    "sensorValues": [1,2,3,4,5],
    "footprint": 4521.609615023,
    "timestamp": 1654531549,
    "daynum": 2459737.170706,
    "solar_lat": 22.696540649846,
    "solar_lon": 298.23268983658,
    "units": "kilometers"
}"""

JSON_rootNode_retainHigherElement=3D"""[{
  "CurrentConditions": {
    "CurrentTime": 1747433679,
    "TempF":  "43.0",
    "TempC":  "6.0",
    "WindKph":  3,
    "WindMph":  2,
    "WindGustsMph":  7,
    "WindGustsKph":  11
  },
  "SensorName": "Oak Park"
}]"""

with socket.socket(socket.AF_INET, socket.SOCK_STREAM) as s:
    s.bind((HOST, PORT))
    s.listen()
    print(f"Server listening on {HOST}:{PORT}")
    #message =3D esriJSON.encode('utf-8')
    #message =3D XML.encode('utf-8')
    #message =3D XML_objectFlattening.encode('utf-8')
    #message =3D XML_arrayFlattening.encode('utf-8')
    #message =3D JSON.encode('utf-8')
    #message =3D JSON_objectFlattening.encode('utf-8')
    #message =3D JSON_arrayFlattening.encode('utf-8')
    message =3D JSON_rootNode_retainHigherElement.encode('utf-8')
    #message =3D geoJSON.encode('utf-8')
    #message =3D delimitedComma
    #message =3D delimitedPipe
    #message =3D delimitedSemiColon
    #message =3D delimitedTab
    #message =3D delimitedSemiColonEnvelopeGeometry


    while True:
        print("Waiting for a client to connect...")
        conn, addr =3D s.accept()  # Accept a new connection
        with conn:
            print(f"Connected by {addr}")
            while True:
                try:
                    if message in (delimitedComma, delimitedPipe, delimited=
SemiColon, delimitedTab, delimitedSemiColonEnvelopeGeometry):
                        conn.sendall(message.encode('utf-8') + RECORD_TERMI=
NATOR)
                    else:
                        conn.sendall(message)
                    print(message)
                    time.sleep(INTERVAL_SECONDS)
                except (BrokenPipeError, ConnectionResetError, ConnectionAb=
ortedError):
                    # ConnectionResetError is Linux, ConnectionAbortedError=
 is Windows
                    print("Client disconnected.")
                    break       </pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>SocketTest</strong></p>
<p>The following steps could be done on the same machine that Velocity is i=
nstalled on or a different machine that is on the same network (i.e. the ma=
chine that Enterprise is installed on)<br>
 NOTE- to get SocketTest to work with the TCP Client Feed, you will have to=
 first start running SocketTest, start the feed in Velocity and wait for te=
stConnection.&nbsp; You will have to start listening again and send a sampl=
e message with the data that you want to send.&nbsp; This will satisfy samp=
leMessages.&nbsp; We have to do this because Velocity terminates the connec=
tion with the TCP Server between testConnection and sampleMessages.&nbsp; S=
ocketTest is not designed to handle the terminated connection.</p>
<p>The following steps could be done on the same machine that Velocity is i=
nstalled on or a different machine that is on the same network (i.e. the ma=
chine that Enterprise is installed on)</p>
<ol>
<li>Download open JDK from&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://=
jdk.java.net/24/" rel=3D"nofollow">here&nbsp;</a></li>
<li>Extract Open JDK and make note of the file path</li>
<li>Download the zip file for SocketTest from&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-lin=
k" href=3D"https://esriis-my.sharepoint.com/:u:/g/personal/joa10132_esri_co=
m/EVlrGQmQHQRJju-JvM3PCQ8BSL-bps7ZkFOccxaB4VLmvg?e=3DBiWoV3" rel=3D"nofollo=
w">here</a></li>
<li>Unzip the file and edit the file called&nbsp; SocketTest.bat in Notepad=
 or similar application</li>
<li>To the .bat file, ADD 2 lines to the beginning.&nbsp; Your final .bat f=
ile will have 7 lines total:=20
<ol>
<li><code>@set JAVA_HOME=3D"C:\Users\joa10132\Downloads\jdk-24.0.1"</code>&=
nbsp; where you replace the file directory with the location that you unzip=
ped Open JDK.</li>
<li><code>@set Path=3D"C:\Users\joa10132\Downloads\jdk-24.0.1\bin";%Path%</=
code>&nbsp; where you replace the file directory with the location of the b=
in directory</li>
</ol></li>
<li>Run SocketTest app using your the updating configuration from the .bat =
file.&nbsp; To do this, use the command line to:=20
<ol>
<li>cd to the location of the SocketTest application</li>
<li>Run<span>&nbsp;</span><code>.\SocketTest.bat</code>&nbsp; &nbsp;This wi=
ll run SocketTest app using the customized .bat file</li>
</ol></li>
<li>To use SocketTest to test the TCP Client Feed:&nbsp;=20
<ol>
<li>In Velocity, create the TCP feed using 127.0.0.1 as the address and 500=
5 as the port.&nbsp; Select 'Next', and notice that SocketTest will receive=
 the request</li>
<li>Start listening in SocketTest and send a sample message with the schema=
 of the data.</li>
<li>Velocity will use the message to derive the schema</li>
<li>Start the feed and use SocketTest to manually send messages</li>
</ol></li>
</ol>
<h2 id=3D"TCPClient(Enterpriseonly)-Requirements">Requirements</h2>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"panel" style=3D"background-color: WhiteSmoke;border-color: bl=
ack;border-style: solid;border-width: 2px;">
<div class=3D"panelHeader" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 2px;border-bottom-=
style: solid;border-bottom-color: black;background-color: white;color: blac=
k;"><b>Git Markdown for Devtopia issue test task</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"panelContent" style=3D"background-color: WhiteSmoke;">
<p>[Confluence wiki page can be found here](<a href=3D"https://confluencewi=
kidev.esri.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=3D452624823" rel=3D"nofollow">T=
CP Client Feed</a>)<br>
 ***<br>
 - **Properties** &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] host &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] port &nbsp;<br>
 - **Schema and data configurations support** &nbsp;<br>
 - **Field types** &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] String &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Date &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Int32 &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Int64 &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Float32 &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Float64 &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Boolean &nbsp;<br>
 - **Date and time** &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Date format &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; - [x] No Date &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; - [x] Epoch milliseconds &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; - [x] Epoch seconds &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; - [x] Other (string) &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Start time &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] End time &nbsp;<br>
 - **Location types** &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Geometry type: Point &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Geometry type: Line &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Geometry type: Polygon &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Geometry type: Multipoint &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Geometry type: Envelope &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Geometry type: None &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Single geometry field: Coordinates &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Single geometry field: Geometry from EsriJSON &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Single geometry field: Geometry from GeoJSON &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Single geometry field: Geometry from WKT &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] X/Y field: Point from lat long &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Z values &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Spatial reference &nbsp;<br>
 - **Tracking** &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] No track ID &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Track ID &nbsp;<br>
 - **Time types** &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] No time &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Instant time (start_time only) &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] Interval time (start_time, end_time) &nbsp;<br>
 - **Data formats supported** &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - Delimited &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; - [x] Comma &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; - [x] Semi-colon &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; - [x] Pipe &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; - [x] Tab &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] EsriJSON &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] GeoJSON &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] XML &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; - [x] Root node &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; - [x] Object Flattening &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; - [x] Object Flattening exemptions &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; - [ ] Array flattening&nbsp; (waiting on pbi to be fixed)<br=
>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; - [ ] Array flattening exemptions&nbsp; (waiting on pbi to b=
e fixed)<br>
 &nbsp; - [x] JSON &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; - [x] Root node &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; - [x] Flattening &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; - [x] Flattening exemptions &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; - [x] Array flattening &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; - [x] Array flattening exemptions &nbsp;<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; - [x] Retain Higher Element<br><br><br></p>
</div>
</div>
